{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01WPvzZ2axgs4EJwCVr53c6t","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Here's the implementation:\n\n## Analysis\n\nThe `shouldIgnorePod` method in `pod_model.go:437-443` excludes pods from scheduling gate assignment when `pod.HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` returns true. Pods in `openshift-kube-apiserver` are kube-apiserver pods that target control-plane nodes via `node-role.kubernetes.io/master` node selectors. This means they're excluded from gating even when the CPPC's `namespaceSelector` is nil (i.e., matches all namespaces).\n\n## File to modify\n\n**`internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook_test.go`** — full replacement:\n\n```go\npackage podplacement\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\timgspecv1 \"github.com/opencontainers/image-spec/specs-go/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/image/fake/registry\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Internal/Controller/PodPlacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook\", func() {\n\tWhen(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\", func() {\n\t\tContext(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should ignore pods with a non-empty nodeName\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"test-namespace\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeName(\"test-node-name\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t\tContext(\"is handling a pod in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should not assign the scheduling gate even when the namespaceSelector matches all namespaces\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tBy(\"Creating the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\")\n\t\t\t\tns := &corev1.Namespace{}\n\t\t\t\tns.Name = \"openshift-kube-apiserver\"\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, ns)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create namespace\", err)\n\n\t\t\t\tBy(\"Creating a pod with a control-plane node selector in openshift-kube-apiserver\")\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeSelectors(utils.MasterNodeSelectorLabel, \"\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr = k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\n\t\t\t\tBy(\"Verifying the scheduling gate was not assigned\")\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).NotTo(ContainElement(corev1.PodSchedulingGate{\n\t\t\t\t\tName: utils.SchedulingGateName,\n\t\t\t\t}), \"pod in openshift-kube-apiserver should not have the scheduling gate\")\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Labels).To(HaveKeyWithValue(utils.SchedulingGateLabel, utils.LabelValueNotSet),\n\t\t\t\t\t\"scheduling gate label should indicate the pod was not gated\")\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n## What changed\n\n1. **Added imports**: `corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"` (for `Namespace` and `PodSchedulingGate`) and `\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"` (for `MasterNodeSelectorLabel`, `SchedulingGateName`, `SchedulingGateLabel`, `LabelValueNotSet`).\n\n2. **Added a new `Context` block** as a sibling to the existing `\"is handling the mutation of pods\"` Context, inside the existing `When(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\"` block.\n\n3. The new test:\n   - Creates the `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace (it's not created in `seedK8S`)\n   - Builds a pod using the fluent builder API with `WithNodeSelectors(utils.MasterNodeSelectorLabel, \"\")` — this sets the `node-role.kubernetes.io/master` node selector, which triggers `HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` in `shouldIgnorePod` (`pod_model.go:434`)\n   - Asserts the scheduling gate is **not** present in `pod.Spec.SchedulingGates`\n   - Asserts the `multiarch.openshift.io/scheduling-gate` label is `\"not-set\"` (confirming the webhook processed the pod but chose to ignore it)\n\n## Why the pod is excluded\n\nThe webhook's `Handle` method calls `shouldIgnorePod` (`pod_model.go:437`), which returns `true` when `pod.HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` is true (`pod_model.go:439`). This check (`models/pod.go:134`) matches pods with `node-role.kubernetes.io/master` or `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` in their `spec.nodeSelector`. The existing CPPC created in `SynchronizedBeforeSuite` has no `namespaceSelector` (nil = matches all namespaces), satisfying the \"even when namespaceSelector matches all\" condition.\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# From the repo root:\nmake unit\n```\n\nOr to run just the webhook test:\n\n```bash\nKUBEBUILDER_ASSETS=\"$(./bin/setup-envtest use 1.36.0 --bin-dir ./bin -p path)\" \\\n  go run ./vendor/github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2/ginkgo -vv \\\n    --label-filter integration \\\n    ./internal/controller/podplacement/...\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1079,"cache_read_input_tokens":83964,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1079,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe060d4d-c532-483e-98fb-febed5f676a7","uuid":"ea3ea5f5-5115-4f17-b476